-- China’s Wu Urges Diplomatic Solution to Iran Nuclear Standoff
-- B y   J a m e s   G .   N e u g e r
-- 2012-03-09T15:15:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-09/china-s-wu-urges-diplomatic-solution-to-iran-nuclear-standoff.html
Wu Hailong, China’s ambassador to
the European Union, said a diplomatic solution is needed in the
international standoff over  Iran’s nuclear program .  “I couldn’t think of a worse proposal to resolve the
Iranian issue than by resorting to force,” Wu told reporters
today in Brussels. He called on Iran to show flexibility and
work with international community.  On the potential impact on  oil prices , Wu said, “I don’t
know what kind of disaster there could be.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
James G. Neuger in Brussels at 
 jneuger@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
